  <h2>FAQs About Word Counting</h2>
  <p><strong>Does punctuation count as a word?</strong> No. Only words (letters/numbers separated by spaces) count. A period, comma, or hyphen is not a word.</p>

  <p><strong>How do I count words in PDF files?</strong> Copy the text from your PDF, paste into a word counter, and get instant statistics.</p>

  <p><strong>Can I count words in a Google Doc?</strong> Google Docs has a built-in word counter (Tools > Word Count), but TextWonder's counter provides more detailed stats.</p>
